# Secret store — never commit real credentials.  All outbound secrets
# (NickServ/SASL/server/oper passwords, API keys, the User-Agent email)
# live here once you run:  python -m secret_store migrate
#
# config.ini is tracked as a credential-free template; real values go
# into the OS keyring (preferred) or secrets.ini (0600, this file).
secrets.ini
secrets.ini.tmp

# Personal non-secret overrides (server hostname, user_modes, admin
# password hash).  Loaded on top of config.ini by config.py.
config.local.ini
